Create Slicer Panel 14

 Create Slicer Panel

  1. Click on the Slicer Visualization and drag quarter(OccurredDate Date Hierarchy) to the Field
  2. Select the Dropdown option
  3. Reduce size
  4. Click on the formatting pane and make the following settings: switch off Category, switch on Title - Text = Quarter, Font Color = white, Background color = blue, Centre Alignment
  5. Click on the Slicer Visualization and drag Month(OccurredDate Date Hierarchy) to the Field
  6. Repeat 2 to 4 to create Month slicer
  7. Insert the rectangle shape and drag both the Quarter and Month slicer into it
  8. Insert the left-back button, reduce and drag into the rectangle
  9. Click on View and then Selection and Bookmark to insert the Selection and Bookmark pane
  10. On the Selection pane, drag both Slicers above Shape
  11. Select the left-back button, both Slicers, and Shape, click on format and then group to group them together
  12. Rename the group to Calendar on the Selection Pane
  13. On the Bookmark pane, click on add and rename to show Calendar, click on the ellipse and uncheck data
  14.  On the Selection pane, click on Hide to hide the Calendar Group 
  15. On the Bookmark pane, click on add and rename to Hide Calendar, click on the ellipse and uncheck data
  16. Insert the Calendar Image and turn on Action on the Format image pane
  17. On the Action Dropdown : Type = Bookmark, Bookmark = show Calendar, Tooltip = Show Calendar
  18. Click on the left back button in the group and then switch on Action on the format image pane
  19. On the Action Dropdown : Type = Bookmark, Bookmark = show Calendar, Tooltip = Show Calendar


Create Crime Slicer Panel

  1. Create District Slicer (DistrictName from NewChicagoDistrict) and Primary Type Slice(Primary Type from ChicagoCrimeData) as described in 1 to 6 above
  2. Follow 7 to 19 to create the Crime Slicer Panel
